{
  "texts": [
    "Time complexities for both the pre-processing and condensing phases are assessed separately and the condensing procedure is further divided into forward propagation, process execution, loss calculation, condensed graph updating, and relay model updating.",
    "Following GCond [26], the relay model f θ for all strategies is a L layer SGC [17] incorporating a linear model with the hidden dimension denoted by h. For the original graph, N, M, d, and C are the number of nodes, edges, feature dimensions, and classes, respectively.",
    "The number of nodes in the condensed graph is represented by N ′.",
    "For a fair comparison, the pre-defined adjacency matrix [29] is utilized across all methods.",
    "The pre-processing stage for gradient matching [26], kernel ridge regression [64] and distribution matching [48] incorporates non-parametric graph convolution."
  ]
}